# Component Design Patterns

## Nielsen Heuristics Checklist (attach relevant ones as JSDoc)

Every component must address relevant heuristics:

```ts
/**
 * MyComponent (Molecule)
 * H1: Visibility of System Status — hover states, loading indicators
 * H3: User Control & Freedom — focus states, keyboard navigation
 * H4: Consistency & Standards — uniform spacing and color usage
 * H6: Recognition Rather Than Recall — visual affordances
 * H8: Aesthetic & Minimalist Design — no decorative excess
 */
```

## Accessibility Requirements

Every interactive component needs:

```tsx
// Keyboard navigation
onKeyDown={(e) => {
  if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
    e.preventDefault()
    handleAction()
  }
}}

// Focus visible (not just focus)
&:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid ${props => props.theme.colors.primary[500]};
  outline-offset: ${props => props.theme.spacing[1]};
  border-radius: ${props => props.theme.radius.sm};
}

// ARIA labels
aria-label="Descriptive action label"
role="button"  // when non-button element is interactive
tabIndex={0}
```

## Motion: Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

```ts
// Every animated component must include this block
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  transition: none;
  animation: none;
  &:hover {
    transform: none;
  }
}
```

## Hover State Pattern

```ts
// Standard card hover (dark mode compatible)
transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;

&:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px);
  border-color: ${props => props.theme.depth?.cardBorderHover ?? props.theme.colors.primary[500]};
  // NO box-shadow in dark mode — border handles elevation
}

// GPU acceleration for animated elements
will-change: transform;
transform: translateZ(0);
```

## Component Size Hierarchy

```
Atom:     Button, Tag, Icon, Input — single responsibility
Molecule: StatCard, ContactButton, SearchBar — 2-3 atoms combined
Organism: ProjectCard, HeroSection — molecules + logic
Template: PageLayout — organisms arranged in grid
Page:     Route-level component — data fetching + template
```

## Styled Component Naming Convention

```ts
// Wrapper (outermost container)
const ComponentWrapper = styled.div``
const ComponentContainer = styled.section``

// Sub-elements: ComponentNoun
const ComponentTitle = styled.h2``
const ComponentContent = styled.div``
const ComponentMeta = styled.span``

// Variants via transient props ($-prefix)
const ComponentItem = styled.li<{ $isActive: boolean; $variant?: 'default' | 'glass' }>`
  // Use $-prefix to prevent prop forwarding to DOM
`
```

## Glass Variant Pattern (for hero/dark overlay contexts only)

```ts
${props => props.$variant === 'glass' && `
  background: ${props.theme.depth?.cardBackground ?? 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)'};
  border: 1px solid ${props.theme.depth?.cardBorder ?? 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06)'};
  color: ${props.theme.colors.hero?.text ?? 'white'};

  &:hover {
    border-color: ${props.theme.depth?.cardBorderHover ?? 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14)'};
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
`}
```

## Image Overlay Pattern

```ts
// Hover overlay on card images — opacity transition, no blur
const ImageOverlay = styled.div`
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 0.3s ease;

  ${ParentCard}:hover & {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }
`
```

## Don'ts

- ❌ Don't use `backdrop-filter: blur()` on cards (modals/overlays only)
- ❌ Don't use inline styles except for dynamic values (tilt transforms, etc.)
- ❌ Don't use `!important`
- ❌ Don't nest more than 3 levels in styled-components
- ❌ Don't use `color: white` — use `theme.colors.hero.text`
- ❌ Don't create one-off color values — add to theme or use neutral scale
